Leningrad orders study into new cargo airport . The local authority of Russia ' s Leningrad region said on Friday it had commissioned a feasibility study from a U . S . firm on turning a former military air base into an international cargo airport . Airis Development Group Inc should finish by October the study of Veshchevo air base , 150 km ( 100 miles ) northwest of the regional capital , St Petersburg . The regional authority said in a statement that the new airport could have capacity of 400 , 000 to 450 , 000 tonnes of cargo per year after possible modernisation to make it the first cargo - only airport in Europe . Officials said earlier this year the upgrade would cost $ 250 million . After the feasibility study , the U . S . firm will seek investors for the project . - - Moscow Newsroom , + 7095 941 8520 
